The West End Grill & Bar in Hammonton, NJ has been the go-to spot for all ages since 1997. Our service is always fast and friendly! We want every customer to come in, kick back, relax and enjoy a menu that covers all the standard grill fare with several regional surprises. Come enjoy cold drinks that take the sting out of those humid Jersey days and a staff that truly pays attention to our customers needs. The idea is to enjoy yourself and come back often. Our bar is a great place to meet up with friends or to bring your business contacts. No matter the reason, you will always be greeted with a smiling face and a welcoming environment. Plantation on Crystal River West 82 | Official Site TAKE ME BACK TO THE HOTEL Menus Photos Events Contact Us Reserve Menu Reserve An Authentic Taste of Crystal River scroll down Dine on the Bounty of Florida's West Coast Sorry due to the recent storms we are closed now.  We hope to be reopened in the Sumner of 2025.  Please check back for updates. From sunrise to sunset, West 82° Bar & Grill offers an inspired menu of fresh seafood and local ingredients, alongside dazzling views of Florida wildlife and water canals. Take a seat in the bright veranda space and choose from a special selection of flavors harvested right from the source, or let us cook your own catch for the ultimate experience. Breakfast Daily 7:00AM – 11:00AM Lunch Monday - Saturday 11:00 AM – 2:00 PM Dinner Daily 5:00 PM – 9:00 PM Chef Corner Treat yourself to an exquisite culinary experience at West 82° prepared by our talented Chef, Maria Hilton. Indulge in her expertly crafted scallop recipes, including the mouthwatering Scallop Scampi and the delectable Scallop Gratin. Recipes Hear From Past Restaurant Guests “Thank you for a great dining experience” “We ate here while staying at the Plantation in Crystal River. The food was delicious!!” Athenapuppy1, TripAdvisor “Great place for breakfast or lunch” “Breakfast buffet is fantastic with fresh choices. Lunch is fantastic. Very relaxing.” Mark W, TripAdvisor “Excellent service and food!” “Couldn’t be happier with our choices, their grouper and cedar plank salmon were absolutely delicious!” Lucitta, TripAdvisor Seasonal Features Locally Sourced Weekly Features Seasonal Features Enjoy the freshest meals and menu selections throughout the entire year with exclusive seasonal features at West 82° Bar & Grill. From fall harvest specials and festive holiday favorites to every flavor in between, choose from inspired seasonal tastes made with Florida flair. Learn More Locally Sourced Whether you’re craving crispy gator bites, shrimp and grits, or chowder made with regional corn and crab, West 82° Bar & Grill is the go-to for local cuisine in Crystal River. From breakfast and bar bites to dinner plates, West 82° Bar & Grill offers classic taste and casual upscale ambiance around the clock. VIEW MENU Weekly Features It’s always a good idea to try something new, particularly when our talented culinary team is plating tasty creations at the restaurant every week. Whether you stop in for our breakfast buffet, lunch, drinks, or dinner and a little dessert, check out our flavorful weekly features and enjoy special selections for a limited time. Learn More You Catch, We'll Cook Cook your own catch at West 82° Bar & Grill! Bring in your own cleaned catch of the day - scallops or fish - and our chef will prepare it for you family-style in one of four ways for dinner. And if you prefer to have your fish for lunch, we’ll plate it up with some house-made chips and coleslaw. Learn More The Bar Drinks & Local Bites Connected directly to the lobby at Plantation on Crystal River, the bar at West 82° offers a classic indoor space for guests looking to unwind after a day of excitement. Enjoy sipping on a glass of wine, a chilled martini, or a cool whiskey cocktail, paired with light bites like smoked fish dip and shrimp fried golden brown. Learn More Overlooking Calm Florida Waterways Located at the back of the resort’s main building, West 82° Bar & Grill offers you picturesque views of palm trees and canals leading out to Kings Bay. Take in the natural landscapes from tall glass windows while you enjoy dinner by flickering candlelight, or a breakfast buffet to fuel your day. Accessibility | West 82 TAKE ME BACK TO THE HOTEL Menus Photos Events Contact Us Reserve Menu Reserve scroll down Accessibility Statement Plantation on Crystal River is in compliance with ADA standards, with accessible rooms and assistive devices on hand. At Plantation on Crystal River, it’s important to us that our website is accessible and easy to use for all persons with disabilities. When creating our website, our development team used software tools to identify web accessibility standards as outlined by the World Wide Web Consortium's Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.0 Level AA (WCAG 2.0 AA). While the industry is not operating from approved, regulated legislation, Plantation on Crystal River is committed to our good faith effort to follow the guidelines available. If you have questions, concerns or have discovered an accessibility issue on our site, please contact us by emailing to piresort@plantationinn.com . Be sure to include specifics and any page where an issue has occurred. We will make every reasonable effort to make the page accessible for you. 9301 West Fort Island Trail Crystal River, Florida , 34429 Phone: 352.795.4211 Ext (88311) © West 82°  2025.
